Manny Pacquiao looked extremely focused during a training session in the Philippines as he stepped up his preparations for his mega-fight against rival Floyd Mayweather.

The 36-year-old was put through his paces on Monday as he worked out at a gym in General Santos City, located in the Philippines' southern island of Mindanao.

Pacquiao, who was dressed in red and blue Nike garments during the session, will fight long-term rival Mayweather in Las Vegas on May 2.

