The American appears to be counting down the days until his bout with Pacquiao as he recently tweeted his 5.61million followers 'May 2, 2015 #TMT (The Money Team)'.

Mayweather's fight against Pacquiao, which will take place in Las Vegas, could cost boxing fans $99.95 (£65) for a subscription to watch the highly-anticipated showdown.

American cable networks Showtime and HBO are planning to charge viewers a record fee to watch the richest fight in history.

Sky, BT, BoxNation and even ITV are set to battle it out to screen the fight in the UK.

With the combined purse for Mayweather and Pacquiao totalling at least $250million (£162m), projections for the value of the event are rising from an initial $300m (£194m) to close on half a billion (£324m).

